nodes.documentation:
@dev Transfer the specified amount of tokens to the specified address.
     Invokes the `tokenFallback` function if the recipient is a contract.
     The token transfer fails if the recipient is a contract
     but does not implement the `tokenFallback` function
     or the fallback function to receive funds.
     *   Compitable wit ERC-20 Standard
     * @param _to    Receiver address.
@param _value Amount of tokens that will be transferred.

allocateConsumerProtectionFund().details: Function to mint tokens allocated for consumer protection to owner address. Owner then sends them to responsible parties

allocateEcoSystemDevelopmentAndOperation.details: Function to mint tokens allocated for Ecosystem development and operations to owner address. Owner then sends them to responsible parties

allocateTeamAndFounderFund().details: Function to mint tokens allocated for team and founders to owner address. Owner then sends them to responsible parties. Tokens are locked for 1 year and can be claimed after 1 year from date of deployment

allowance(address,address).details: Function to check the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

params._spender: address The address which will spend the funds.
params._tokenOwner: address The address which owns the funds.

allowance(address,address).return: A uint256 specifying the amount of tokens still available for the spender.

approve(address,uint256).details: To change the approve amount you first have to reduce the addresses allowance to zero by calling `approve(_spender, 0)` if it is not already 0 to mitigate the race condition described here https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/20#issuecomment-263524729 Recommended is to use increase approval and decrease approval instead     * Requires either that _value of allwance is 0

params._spender: address who is allowed to spend
params._value: the no of tokens spender can spend

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address.

params._tokenOwner: The address to query the balance of.

balanceOf(address).return: A uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address.

burn(uint256).details: Function that burns an amount of the token of a sender. reduces total and current supply. only owner is allowed to burn tokens.

params._value: The amount that will be burn.

params._spender: address who is allowed to spend
params._subtractedValue: the no of tokens deducted to previous allowance If _subtractedValue is greater than prev allowance, allowance becomes 0

emergencyFreezeAllAccounts(bool).details: Freezes or unfreezes the contract this does not check for previous state before applying new state

params._freeze: boolean status. Use true to freeze and false to unfreeze.

freezeAccount(address,bool).details: Freezes or unfreezes an addreess this does not check for previous state before applying new state

params._freeze: boolean status. Use true to freeze and false to unfreeze.
params._target: the address which will be feeezed.

params._addedValue: the no of tokens added to previous allowance
params._spender: address who is allowed to spend

kill(uint256).details: Function to kill the contract. Do transfer all tokens from contract before executing this function.

params._code: uint that prevents accidental calling of the function

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfer the specified amount of tokens to the specified address.     Invokes the `tokenFallback` function if the recipient is a contract.     The token transfer fails if the recipient is a contract     but does not implement the `tokenFallback` function     or the fallback function to receive funds.     *   Compitable wit ERC-20 Standard

params._value: Amount of tokens that will be transferred.

transfer(address,uint256,bytes).details: Transfer the specified amount of tokens to the specified address.     Invokes the `tokenFallback` function if the recipient is a contract.     The token transfer fails if the recipient is a contract     but does not implement the `tokenFallback` function     or the fallback function to receive funds.

params._value: Amount of tokens that will be transferred.

transferAnyERC20Token(address,uint256).details: Function to withdraw any accidently sent ERC20 or 223 Token. the value should be pre-multiplied by decimals of token wthdrawan

params._tokenAddress: address The contract address of ERC20 token.
params._value: uint amount to tokens to be withdrawn

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfer tokens from one address to another.

params._from: address The address from which you want to send tokens.
params._to: address The address to which you want to transfer tokens.
params._value: uint256 the amount of tokens to be transferred.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256,byt.details: Transfer tokens from one address to another.

params._from: address The address from which you want to send tokens.
params._to: address The address to which you want to transfer tokens.
params._value: uint256 the amount of tokens to be transferred

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of contract to other address

params._newOwner: address The address of new owner
